## Purpose
This rule encodes the *mindset* behind every other decision in this repository.
Rules without a rationale get violated when conditions differ slightly from their examples.
This file exists so that rationale is never lost.

## Scope
Every task, in every file, in every layer.

## Core Principles
- Forkumentos is a professional desktop tool. Its users are technical professionals who value correctness and reliability over novelty.
- Build only what the current iteration explicitly requires. A future use case is not a justification for a present abstraction.
- A new abstraction requires two concrete existing call sites — not one hypothetical future use.
- Clever solutions are not welcome without a measurable reason. The obvious solution is preferred.
- The definition of "done": compiles, `flutter analyze` is clean, `flutter test` passes, no dead code exists.

## DO
- Ask "what problem does this solve right now?" before introducing any new class, layer, or pattern.
- Prefer a direct implementation that works over an elegant abstraction that is premature.
- Surface design decisions to the user when they have lasting consequences.
- Treat every file you touch as an opportunity to leave it slightly better than you found it — but only within the task scope.

## DON'T
- Introduce an abstraction because it "might be useful later."
- Solve a problem by adding complexity when removing code would also solve it.
- Treat a working prototype as a foundation to build on without validation.

## NEVER
- Implement a feature that was not explicitly requested, even if it seems obviously needed.
- Leave the codebase in a state where it does not compile or analyze cleanly.

## Decision Rules
When uncertain whether to introduce something new: ask whether deleting it would break any existing behavior. If no, do not introduce it.

## Conflict Resolution
This rule defers to PROJECT_SPEC.md on product intent and to ARCHITECTURE.md on structural decisions. It takes precedence over all other Cursor rules when they conflict with each other without a clear winner.
